Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.17,0:00:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.64,0:00:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight! Mail's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.38,0:00:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.25,0:00:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We just had a really\Nheavy delivery today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.39,0:00:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a deluxe set of Special\NEdition Ogres & Oubliettes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.56,0:00:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,figurines that I'm\Ntotally surprised by
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.16,0:00:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and haven't been hinting\Nthat I need forever!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.23,0:00:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... it's\Nfor Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.33,0:00:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Awww.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.73,0:00:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.03,0:00:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.74,0:00:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh, it's from\NPrincess Celestia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.11,0:00:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So's this. Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.74,0:00:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,She couldn't have\Nput it into the box?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.31,0:00:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,"My Dearest Twilight.\NI have been conducting
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.61,0:00:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a thorough cleaning\Nof the castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.38,0:00:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and I came across a few items\Nof yours in your old room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.58,0:00:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you might\Nwant them back."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.39,0:00:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even know\NI'd left anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.79,0:00:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:00:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember this? It's the\Nmacaroni picture frame
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.93,0:01:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Cadance helped me make\Nwhen I was a filly!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.53,0:01:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could forget a\Nmasterpiece like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.10,0:01:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My G1 Starswirl figure!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.24,0:01:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And some of my favorite\Nschool scrolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.04,0:01:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's my extra,\Nextra credit report
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.51,0:01:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on "The Impediments of Using\NMagic in Everyday Chores"!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.11,0:01:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha! Still so true!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.48,0:01:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is my Smash Fortune\Ncomic in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.39,0:01:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking\Nfor that for years!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.02,0:01:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.26,0:01:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.92,0:01:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, oh no, oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.16,0:01:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? It just looks\Nlike an old library book.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.03,0:01:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! It belongs to\Nthe Canterlot Library.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.43,0:01:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That means it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.74,0:01:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,... OVERDUE!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.28,0:02:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand, Spike!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a perfect library\Nbook-return record!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.58,0:02:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahem. {\i1}Had{\i0} a perfect record.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.59,0:02:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[groan] I've never turned in a\Nbook even a minute late!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.19,0:02:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.42,0:02:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,has been overdue since\NI left for Ponyville!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.11,0:02:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure you bring\Nthis one back on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.71,0:03:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a long\Nwaiting list of ponies
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.08,0:03:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,who can't wait to read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.12,0:03:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise I won't\Nlet you down!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.59,0:03:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Of course you\Nwon't, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's anypony I can\Ntrust to take care of a book,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.09,0:03:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,it's you, Twilight Sparkle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.53,0:03:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you still hold the\N"Best Book Borrower" title.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.83,0:03:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh! I hope I do forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.27,0:03:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Spike! Quick! Find\Nme that old copy of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.01,0:03:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,"Predictions and Prophecies".\NWhat's that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.35,0:03:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it was a gift\Nfor Moondancer but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.42,0:03:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.48,0:03:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You know we don't have time\Nfor that sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.99,0:03:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Celestia\Nsent me to Ponyville
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.76,0:03:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I forgot\Nall about this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.56,0:03:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Dusty Pages prided herself\Nthat no books were damaged
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.36,0:03:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or lost on her watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.83,0:03:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And I failed her!\NI've failed MYSELF!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.27,0:03:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I take it we're\Ngoing to Canterlot?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.81,0:04:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] The sooner the\Nbetter, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.29,0:04:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, why are we hiding?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.22,0:04:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you want to\Nreturn your book?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.06,0:04:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but what if somepony\Nsees me in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.73,0:04:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the Princess\Nof Friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.29,0:04:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everywhere I go,\Nponies recognize me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.53,0:04:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll stick out\Nlike a sore hoof!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.53,0:04:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Twilight Sparkle in\Na library? Stop the presses!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.90,0:04:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A late book is a\Nbig deal, Spike!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.17,0:04:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What if Dusty Pages\Nrevokes my library card?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Or bans me from ever\Nentering the building again!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.58,0:04:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you already have\Nmost of those books
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.15,0:04:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in your collection at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.62,0:04:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but the ones in\Nthere have a special
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.82,0:04:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Canterlot Library-y smell!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.22,0:04:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You sniff books?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.52,0:04:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.79,0:04:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to LIVE in a library!\NIf I'm not a good example
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.96,0:04:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of proper book-borrowing\Nbehavior,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.97,0:04:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,then what kind of\Nprincess am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.47,0:05:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,One that makes mistakes\Nlike everypony else.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.17,0:05:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust me, once you return that\Nbook, you'll feel way better.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.11,0:05:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.38,0:05:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.51,0:05:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.00,0:05:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[disguised voice]\NAhem. I have a book to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Twilight!\NSo good to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.59,0:05:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Need some recommendations\Nfrom the new release section?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.81,0:05:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] Is that the\Nnew edition of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.71,0:05:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mooncurve's Seven\NTheories on Bending Time"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.21,0:05:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been waiting\Nfor the release since--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.35,0:05:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhh I mean, uh, no\Nbooks today, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.55,0:05:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do need to speak with\NDusty Pages about a... [ahem]
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.99,0:05:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,sensitive matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.79,0:05:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Dusty who?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.23,0:06:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Dusty Pages! The head librarian?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.46,0:06:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She's worked here forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.57,0:06:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Princess.\NI don't know her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.37,0:06:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, was there some\Nother way I can help
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.47,0:06:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the Library's Best\NBook Borrower?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.11,0:06:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Just ask her where to\Nreturn an overdue book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.41,0:06:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no big deal. It\Nhappens all the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.98,0:06:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to me, it doesn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.49,0:06:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[sigh] Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.62,0:06:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine! Oh, no. I didn't even\Nthink about the late fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.66,0:06:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A book out this long\Nwill probably cost
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.13,0:06:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand bits!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.23,0:06:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She--I mean {\i1}we{\i0}, have\Nan overdue book.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.03,0:06:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Well, that's no\Nproblem at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it happens\Nall the time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.24,0:06:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.54,0:06:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just find it\Nin the card catalog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.81,0:06:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Er.. Number one-eight-nine-oh-five. Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.15,0:06:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ohhhhh, wow. Eeeesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.55,0:06:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't seen a book\Nthis late in, well, ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.89,0:07:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahem. You need to go and\Nsee First Folio
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.89,0:07:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,in the "Grossly Overdue\NBook Return Office
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for Ponies Who\NShould Know Better."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't pull any punches\Nwith those names, do ya?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.00,0:07:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And that office would be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.20,0:07:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In the basement.\N[whispers] Because of the SHAME.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.14,0:07:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa. Ugh. Looks like nopony\Never goes down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.25,0:07:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Nopony except\Nundependable rule breakers
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.72,0:07:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who deserve all the\Nhorrors this hallway holds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.25,0:07:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And their faithful\Ndragon companions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.02,0:07:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh. Hey, looks like First Folio\Nleft a note on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.83,0:07:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandon hope all\Nye who enter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.86,0:07:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"Out to lunch on\NRestaurant Row."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.23,0:07:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess we'll have\Nto try back later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.17,0:07:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! I can't wait another\Nminute to return this book!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.64,0:07:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In the time it took\Nus to get there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.91,0:07:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I racked up another--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.51,0:07:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Seventeen bits in late fees!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:07:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.21,0:07:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, cause I'm starving!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.52,0:08:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. You mean to\Nfind First Folio.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.52,0:08:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we at least\Nget take-out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.69,0:08:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me if you see any\Nlibrarian-type ponies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.33,0:08:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight, we've\Ntried this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.49,0:08:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,at three other\Nrestaurants already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.63,0:08:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And my late fines\Nare already up
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.36,0:08:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,another 26 more bits!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.10,0:08:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Waiter, we're\Nready to order.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.61,0:08:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm not actually a---
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.91,0:08:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Three samosas, two\Ncurry specials...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.28,0:08:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that's\Nenough for the two of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.24,0:08:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. I would probably order some\NNaan as well? For the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.68,0:08:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds great!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.22,0:08:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight? Is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.52,0:08:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Moondancer! How\Nhave you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.05,0:08:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just visiting.\NNo real reason. Heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.36,0:08:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's good to see you!\NI'm just meeting my friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.09,0:08:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,First Folio, for lunch.\NDo you want to join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,First Folio!? YES!\NI mean, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.27,0:08:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Twilight!\NGood to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.54,0:08:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know your picture\Nis still up in our library
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.77,0:09:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,as the Best Book Borrower.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.11,0:09:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeeeeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.13,0:09:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping I could talk\Nto Dusty Pages about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.95,0:09:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Dusty Pages left\Nthe library moons ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.62,0:09:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.88,0:09:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm mm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.02,0:09:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I heard she was\Nforced to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.19,0:09:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so sad. She\Nloved the library.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.99,0:09:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. {\i1}Forced{\i0} to leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.53,0:09:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh huh, yeah. She had a\Nperfect librarian record,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.60,0:09:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,until one careless pony\Ndidn't return a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.17,0:09:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruined it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.00,0:09:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you OK, Twilight?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.87,0:09:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh huh... Would...\Nyou excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.91,0:09:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you only order\Nspicy if you can take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.05,0:09:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.55,0:09:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dusty Pages isn't working\Nat the library anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.95,0:09:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because I didn't\Nreturn this book!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.06,0:09:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Spike! I think I got her FIRED!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.83,0:10:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight! The\Nlibrary is that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.47,0:10:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Change of plans! We're\Ngoing to Dusty's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.31,0:10:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She used to invite me\Nover for tea all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.91,0:10:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But what about your late fees?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.81,0:10:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not as important\Nas making things right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.51,0:10:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, so you're not\Ngoing to return the book?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.65,0:10:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Dusty Pages is! It's\Nmy fault she lost her job.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.05,0:10:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I give her the book,\Nshe can get her old job back!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll fix everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't ya see the sign?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.70,0:10:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"No Salesponies"!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm not\Nselling anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.04,0:10:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No carolers either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.78,0:10:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No surveys, no petitions,\Nno free literature--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.65,0:10:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.59,0:10:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just looking for somepony\Nwho used to live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.02,0:10:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure\Nthis was her house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.16,0:10:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Dusty Pages?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.86,0:10:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.76,0:11:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.60,0:11:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She moved to Silver somethin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.87,0:11:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoals? Seas? Surfer? Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.10,0:11:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When you find her,\Ngive her this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.47,0:11:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been stackin' up\Nfor years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.24,0:11:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And tell her to\NCHANGE. HER. ADDRESS!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.86,0:12:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"Silverstable Community..\Nfor the best Golden Years."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.30,0:12:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This HAS to be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.90,0:12:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.07,0:12:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the last "Silver" spot\Non the map we haven't looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.61,0:12:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! This place is--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.64,0:12:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Terrible, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.28,0:12:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's not a single\Nbookshelf in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.48,0:12:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor Dusty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.65,0:12:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. How may I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.06,0:12:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a resident\Nnamed Dusty Pages?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.76,0:12:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes! Her apartment\Nis in the next complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.96,0:12:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ground floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.76,0:12:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.83,0:12:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe that my\Ncarelessness sent her here
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.90,0:12:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,when she could be\Nhappily surrounded
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.47,0:12:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,by millions of\Nwonderful-smelling books!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.24,0:12:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that might just\Nbe a "you" thing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.88,0:13:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp]\NThere she is! Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.56,0:13:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Aarrgghh!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.03,0:13:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She's bound to\Nbe back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.63,0:13:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we should just wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.50,0:13:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We are\Nfixing this... NOW!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.67,0:13:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This place isn't that\Nbig. We can find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.95,0:13:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to interrupt your\Nplein air painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.31,0:13:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but we're looking for Dusty\NPages. Have you seen her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.35,0:13:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure have.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.39,0:13:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.06,0:13:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,She had to leave\Nearly to get to her
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.70,0:13:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,fengbi de ti session.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.90,0:13:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is right\Nbefore she leads
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.70,0:13:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the woodworking\Nclass with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.90,0:13:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she's on\Nto windsurfing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.97,0:14:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh! And don't forget theatre rehearsal!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.21,0:14:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Dusty's playing the\Nlead role... again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.58,0:14:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's her\Nband practice later.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.55,0:14:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.88,0:14:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, Dusty sounds\Nlike one busy pony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.89,0:14:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oooh! She's just filling her\Ndays with distractions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.52,0:14:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to cover the pain of\Nlosing the best job ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.73,0:14:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But not for long!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.26,0:15:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,DUSTY PAGES! Finally!\NC'mon, Spike.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.89,0:15:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! She looks\Npretty happy up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.17,0:15:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust me, it's\Nall an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.97,0:15:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll be a lot happier\Nwhen I deliver the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.10,0:15:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that she can go back to\Nworking at the library!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.51,0:15:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Care to take five, everypony?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.71,0:15:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Twilight Sparkle? My stars!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.65,0:15:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so wonderful to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.75,0:15:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you\Ndoing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.62,0:15:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking all\Nover Equestria for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.16,0:15:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to tell\Nyou something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.09,0:16:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You brought my\Nmail! Oh, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.90,0:16:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I mean, yes, we did, but\Nthat's not why we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.07,0:16:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I let you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.34,0:16:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can't forgive myself\Nuntil I set things right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.37,0:16:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember you\Ndoing anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.61,0:16:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You told me to take special\Ncare of a book I checked out
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.04,0:16:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Canterlot library.\NAnd I never brought it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.31,0:16:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,[gasp] It was YOU that\Nhad that book out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.08,0:16:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The one that broke\Nmy perfect record?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.55,0:16:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But now you can bring\Nit to Canterlot Library
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.92,0:16:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and get your job back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.13,0:16:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.23,0:16:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't ever need to\Nsee that library again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.53,0:16:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you'll excuse me,\NI have somewhere to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.54,0:16:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.55,0:16:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.85,0:16:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If Dusty Pages won't go\Nback to Canterlot Library
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.35,0:16:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and explain everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.42,0:17:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,then she won't be able\Nto get her job back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.52,0:17:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Even worse, her record\Nwill remain... imperfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.09,0:17:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And yours will, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.26,0:17:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well. Yeah! But that\Ndoesn't matter anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.13,0:17:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe a little\Nbit. Oh, no... BITS!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.63,0:17:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The late fines! How\Nmuch do I owe now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.64,0:17:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... You don't want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.43,0:17:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It would have been worth\Nall the bits in Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.61,0:17:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,if I'd made things\Nright with Dusty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.65,0:17:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I knew why\Nshe won't go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.15,0:17:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you ask her?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.52,0:17:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't seem\Nto want to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.49,0:17:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You surprised her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.82,0:17:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And she probably had something\Nelse on her schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.06,0:17:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That thing is PACKED. C'mon,\Nwhat've you got to lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.80,0:17:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I've messed\Nup this much. Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.83,0:17:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, Spike.\NIt's worth a try.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.30,0:17:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you think she\Nwent? Crochet, bingo...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.41,0:17:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A squishy fruit\Nfoodfight tournament!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.14,0:17:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, everypony! We come in--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.21,0:18:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...er pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.76,0:18:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! We just wanna talk to\NDusty Pages for a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.86,0:18:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Please?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.19,0:18:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,TIME OUT!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.63,0:18:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oof!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.73,0:18:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, you should rent gear!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.24,0:18:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not actually\Nhere for the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.27,0:18:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I.. was hoping you'd\Ngive me another chance
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.21,0:18:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk to you about\Nthe library book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.41,0:18:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This really means a\Nlot to you, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.78,0:18:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm hm. I know I\Nruined your life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.01,0:18:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,by not returning\Nmy book on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.02,0:18:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will do anything I\Ncan to make it up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.79,0:18:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Even promise to never take a\Nbook out of the library again,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.99,0:18:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.99,0:18:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That.. is not the\Nreaction we expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.13,0:18:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight, dear. You've\Ngot it all backwards!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.63,0:18:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not upset with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:18:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.24,0:19:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No! If I'm mad at\Nanypony, it's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.11,0:19:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All those years I spent\Nhiding away in that library,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.92,0:19:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to be perfect...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.92,0:19:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When your book never came in,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.55,0:19:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt something.. exhilarating!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.12,0:19:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.36,0:19:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Freedom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.73,0:19:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,From books?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.13,0:19:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,From perfection!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.96,0:19:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I was too stubborn to know\Nwhen to call it quits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.73,0:19:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It took your mistake\Nto make me realize
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.27,0:19:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wasn't living\Nthe life I wanted!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.21,0:19:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean you weren't fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.07,0:19:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You left the library\Nbecause you wanted to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.48,0:19:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Twilight, your late\Nbook was the best thing
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.65,0:19:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that ever happened to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.45,0:19:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm not afraid to try\Nthings I might fail at.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.49,0:19:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, sometimes messing up
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.45,0:19:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,teaches me more than\Ngetting it right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.79,0:19:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sure you don't\Nwant to return it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.22,0:19:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and get that\Nperfect record back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.76,0:19:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.36,0:19:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good. It was\Na yellow one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.16,0:19:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can still\Nsee the words!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.33,0:20:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But it'll have a stain!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't change\Nthe truth inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.54,0:20:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Did you even\Nread that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.84,0:20:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, er... no.\NI guess I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.95,0:20:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,"PERFECTION."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.85,0:20:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next part...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.38,0:20:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Impossible Pursuit."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.09,0:20:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. That might've been\Nuseful to look at earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.80,0:20:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm. Your total late fees come to...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.30,0:20:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,However much it\Nis, I'll cover it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.67,0:20:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, do you have a\Nmonthly payment plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.24,0:20:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...twenty-eight bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.04,0:20:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.28,0:20:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Most ponies don't\Nknow it caps at a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.91,0:20:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably because\Nwe don't tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.59,0:20:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you! Your\Naccount is back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.82,0:20:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we will be taking down
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,your Best Book Borrower picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.33,0:21:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, is that really necessary?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.26,0:21:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It just seems so.. permanent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.50,0:21:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I did return\Nthe book, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.30,0:21:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.37,0:21:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. Letting the perfection go...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You want me to\Nreshelf this for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.67,0:21:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Nope. It's an old edition.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.68,0:21:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already replaced\Nit with a new copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.75,0:21:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, can we keep it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.85,0:21:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be a good\Nreminder to have around.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.18,0:21:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're sure? It's got a stain...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.32,0:21:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what makes it perfect.
